  "instructions": {
    "L": [
      {
        "S": "Dice the 1 Yellow Onion finely and mince the 3 cloves of Garlic. If using the Jalapeno, slice it lengthwise, scrape out the seeds and ribs with a spoon, then finely dice. Wear food-safe gloves or wash hands thoroughly with soap immediately after handling Jalapeno. Avoid touching your eyes or face."
      },
      {
        "S": "Place the diced onion, garlic, and jalapeno in the bottom of a 5 to 6 quart slow cooker. Lay the 1 to 1 1/4 pounds of chicken breasts on top of the aromatics to keep them submerged in liquid for even cooking. Add the 2 drained and rinsed cans of cannellini beans, 1 can of drained and rinsed pinto beans, and 1 cup frozen corn kernels. Sprinkle in the 1 1/2 teaspoons ground cumin, 1 teaspoon dried oregano, 1/2 teaspoon ground coriander, 1/2 teaspoon smoked paprika, 1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper, 1/2 teaspoon kosher salt, and 1/4 teaspoon black pepper."
      },
      {
        "S": "Pour the 16 ounce jar of salsa verde and 2 cups low-sodium chicken broth over everything. Stir gently while keeping the chicken breasts submerged beneath the liquid as much as possible. Place the lid on the slow cooker."
      },
      {
        "S": "Cook on high for 4 hours or on low for 8 hours, until the chicken reaches an internal temperature of 165 degrees F when checked with an instant-read thermometer."
      },
      {
        "S": "Remove the chicken breasts carefully to a cutting board using tongs or a slotted spoon. Use two forks to shred the hot meat into bite-sized pieces."
      },
      {
        "S": "Add the 4 ounces of softened cream cheese cubes directly to the hot chili and stir until melted and fully incorporated, about 1 to 2 minutes. Mash about one-third of the beans against the side of the slow cooker using the back of a wooden spoon or a potato masher to thicken the chili. Return the shredded chicken to the pot. Stir in the 1 tablespoon fresh lime juice and 2 tablespoons chopped fresh cilantro if using. Taste and adjust salt and pepper as needed."
      },
      {
        "S": "Ladle into bowls and top with your favorites such as shredded Monterey Jack or pepper jack cheese, diced avocado, a squeeze of fresh lime, sour cream or Greek yogurt, fresh cilantro, sliced scallions, and tortilla chips or strips."
      }
    ]
  },
  "notes": {
    "L": [
      {
        "S": "Make-ahead and Freezer-friendly: This chili stores well in the refrigerator for up to 4 days and freezes beautifully for up to 3 months. Omit the cream cheese and lime juice if freezing. Stir those in when reheating."
      },
      {
        "S": "Chicken thighs option: Boneless skinless thighs are even more forgiving in a slow cooker and will not dry out. Use the same weight."
      },
      {
        "S": "Low-sodium tip: Between the broth, salsa verde, and canned beans, sodium can add up. Using low-sodium broth and tasting before adding salt is important."
      },
      {
        "S": "Vegetarian adaptation: Omit the chicken. Add an extra can of beans and increase the frozen corn to 1 1/2 cups for a hearty vegetarian version."
      },
      {
        "S": "Scaling up: Recipe doubles easily for a larger slow cooker (6+ quart). Cook time remains the same."
      },
      {
        "S": "Gluten-Free: This recipe is naturally gluten-free. Verify that your salsa verde and chicken broth are certified gluten-free, as some brands may contain wheat-based thickeners or additives."
      }
    ]
  },
